method.name: connectCamera
method.comment: This method is invoked shall perform concrete operation to initialize the camera. CONTRACT: as a result of this method variables mFrameWidth and mFrameHeight MUST be initialized with the size of the Camera frames that will be delivered to external processor. width: - the width of this SurfaceView height: - the height of this SurfaceView

method.name: disableView
method.comment: This method is provided for clients, so they can disable camera connection and stop the delivery of frames even though the surface view itself is not destroyed and still stays on the scren

method.name: disconnectCamera
method.comment: Disconnects and release the particular camera object being connected to this surface view. Called when syncObject lock is held

method.name: setMaxFrameSize
method.comment: This method sets the maximum size that camera frame is allowed to be. When selecting size - the biggest size which less or equal the size set will be selected. As an example - we set setMaxFrameSize(200,200) and we have 176x152 and 320x240 sizes. The preview frame will be selected with 176x152 size. This method is useful when need to restrict the size of preview frame for some reason (for example for video recording) maxWidth: - the maximum width allowed for camera frame. maxHeight: - the maximum height allowed for camera frame

method.name: calculateCameraFrameSize
method.comment: This helper method can be called by subclasses to select camera preview size. It goes over the list of the supported preview sizes and selects the maximum one which fits both values set via setMaxFrameSize() and surface frame allocated for this view supportedSizes: surfaceWidth: surfaceHeight: Return type: @return:optimal frame size

method.name: enableView
method.comment: This method is provided for clients, so they can enable the camera connection. The actual onCameraViewStarted callback will be delivered only after both this method is called and surface is available

method.name: matToBitmap
method.comment:
Converts OpenCV Mat to Android Bitmap.
This function converts an image in the OpenCV Mat representation to the Android Bitmap. The input Mat object has to be of the types 'CV_8UC1' (gray-scale), 'CV_8UC3' (RGB) or 'CV_8UC4' (RGBA). The output Bitmap object has to be of the same size as the input Mat and of the types 'ARGB_8888' or 'RGB_565'. This function throws an exception if the conversion fails. mat: is a valid input Mat object of types 'CV_8UC1', 'CV_8UC3' or 'CV_8UC4'. bmp: is a valid Bitmap object of the same size as the Mat and of type 'ARGB_8888' or 'RGB_565'. premultiplyAlpha: is a flag, that determines, whether the Mat needs to be converted to alpha premultiplied format (like Android keeps 'ARGB_8888' bitmaps); the flag is ignored for 'RGB_565' bitmaps.

method.name: matToBitmap1
method.comment: Short form of the matToBitmap(mat, bmp, premultiplyAlpha=false) mat: is a valid input Mat object of the types 'CV_8UC1', 'CV_8UC3' or 'CV_8UC4'. bmp: is a valid Bitmap object of the same size as the Mat and of type 'ARGB_8888' or 'RGB_565'.

method.name: bitmapToMat1
method.comment: Short form of the bitmapToMat(bmp, mat, unPremultiplyAlpha=false). bmp: is a valid input Bitmap object of the type 'ARGB_8888' or 'RGB_565'. mat: is a valid output Mat object, it will be reallocated if needed, so Mat may be empty.

method.name: bitmapToMat
method.comment:
Converts Android Bitmap to OpenCV Mat.
This function converts an Android Bitmap image to the OpenCV Mat. ARGB_8888' and 'RGB_565' input Bitmap formats are supported. The output Mat is always created of the same size as the input Bitmap and of the 'CV_8UC4' type, it keeps the image in RGBA format. This function throws an exception if the conversion fails. bmp: is a valid input Bitmap object of the type 'ARGB_8888' or 'RGB_565'. mat: is a valid output Mat object, it will be reallocated if needed, so it may be empty. unPremultiplyAlpha: is a flag, that determines, whether the bitmap needs to be converted from alpha premultiplied format (like Android keeps 'ARGB_8888' ones) to regular one; this flag is ignored for 'RGB_565' bitmaps.

field.name: octave
field.comment: Octave (pyramid layer), from which the keypoint has been extracted.

field.name: size
field.comment: Diameter of the useful keypoint adjacent area.

field.name: response
field.comment: The response, by which the strongest keypoints have been selected. Can be used for further sorting or subsampling.

field.name: class_id
field.comment: Object ID, that can be used to cluster keypoints by an object they belong to.

field.name: angle
field.comment: Computed orientation of the keypoint (-1 if not applicable).

field.name: MAX_ITER
field.comment: The maximum number of iterations or elements to compute

field.name: EPS
field.comment: The desired accuracy threshold or change in parameters at which the iterative algorithm is terminated.

field.name: COUNT
field.comment: The maximum number of iterations or elements to compute
